3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - Graph domination is a topic of interest in game theory, and power domination is a variant of domination that has applications in monitoring systems. 
4. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - Graph domination is a topic of interest in network analysis, and power domination has applications in monitoring networks. 
5. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - Maximal planar graphs are a class of graphs that have applications in computational geometry, and this paper presents a result on power domination in this class of graphs.
